{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"4867","heading":"Security management training for officials assigned to a high risk, high threat post","label":"4867 Security management training for officials assigned to a high risk, high threat post","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/ch58/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextGS–14 and GS–15, referred to in subsec. (c)(4), are contained in the General Schedule, which is set out under , Government Organization and Employees.section 5332 of Title 5","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsFor definition of “high risk, high threat post” as used in this section, see .section 4866(d)(2) of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Officials described in subsection (c) who are assigned to a high risk, high threat post shall receive security training described in subsection (b) on a mandatory basis in order to improve the ability of such officials to make security-related management decisions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Security training described","label":"b Security training described","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"development of skills to better evaluate threats;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"effective use of security resources to mitigate such threats; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"improved familiarity of available security resources.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Officials described","label":"c Officials described","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4867/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs4867%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Members of the Senior Foreign Service appointed under section 3942(a)(1) or 3943 of this title or members of the Senior Executive Service (as such term is described in ).section 3132(a)(2) of title 5","not